HEADWORD: cat-o-nine-tails
<hw>cat"-o'-nine"-tails`</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a whip used as an instrument of
punishment consisting of nine pieces of knotted line or cord fastened to
a handle; -- formerly used to flog offenders on the bare back; -- called
also the <altname>cat</altname>. It was used in the British Navy to
maintain discipline on board sailing ships.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

